PRETORIA - A couple who is fighting to have dagga legalised claimed their court proceedings were being delayed. Jules and Myrtle Stobbs were charged with drug possession in 2010, is waiting for a ruling on its evidence summary in the North Gauteng High Court. READ: Man sentenced for dealing dagga in Mpumalanga The duo wants to have dagga legalised for personal use, cultivation and distribution. On Wednesday, the state argued that the evidence presented contained articles which were not written by experts. It also listed inconsistencies in the evidence summaries. eNCA